## 2. Eloquent Models

Models define the **behavior** and **relationships** for each database table. They encapsulate business logic such as XP calculations and streak tracking.

### 2.1 User Model
**File:** [app/Models/User.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/User.php)
The central model for players. It manages gamification state and defines relationships to all user-owned entities.
*   **Key Logic:** [addXP()](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/User.php#121-135) adds experience and automatically triggers level-ups. [updateStreak()](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/User.php#141-161) manages daily login consistency.
```php
class User extends Authenticatable
{
    protected $fillable = [
        'name', 'email', 'password', 'role',
        'level', 'xp', 'total_xp', 'xp_to_next_level',
        'current_streak', 'longest_streak', 'last_activity_date', 'rank_title',
    ];

    // --- Relationships ---
    public function habits() { return $this->hasMany(Habit::class); }
    public function quests() { return $this->hasMany(Quest::class); }
    public function badges() { return $this->belongsToMany(Badge::class, 'user_badges')->withPivot('earned_at'); }
    public function achievements() { return $this->belongsToMany(Achievement::class, 'user_achievements')->withPivot('progress', 'is_completed'); }
    public function guilds() { return $this->belongsToMany(Guild::class, 'guild_members')->withPivot('role', 'contribution_xp'); }

    // --- Core Game Logic ---
    public function addXP(int $amount): void
    {
        $this->xp += $amount;
        $this->total_xp += $amount;
        while ($this->xp >= $this->xp_to_next_level) {
            $this->xp -= $this->xp_to_next_level;
            $this->level++;
            $this->xp_to_next_level = $this->calculateNextLevelXP();
        }
        $this->save();
    }

    public function calculateNextLevelXP(): int
    {
        return (int) floor(1000 * pow(1.2, $this->level - 1));
    }

    public function updateStreak(): void
    {
        $today = now()->toDateString();
        $yesterday = now()->subDay()->toDateString();
        if ($this->last_activity_date === $yesterday) {
            $this->current_streak++;
        } elseif ($this->last_activity_date !== $today) {
            $this->current_streak = 1;
        }
        $this->last_activity_date = $today;
        $this->save();
    }
}
```

### 2.2 Habit Model
**File:** [app/Models/Habit.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/Habit.php)
Represents a recurring task. The [complete()](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Http/Controllers/QuestController.php#111-131) method is called when a user finishes a habit.
*   **Key Logic:** [complete()](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Http/Controllers/QuestController.php#111-131) creates a transactional log, increments streaks, and awards XP to the user.
```php
class Habit extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = [
        'user_id', 'title', 'description', 'difficulty', 
        'xp_reward', 'frequency', 'current_streak', 'longest_streak',
    ];

    public function user() { return $this->belongsTo(User::class); }
    public function completions() { return $this->hasMany(HabitCompletion::class); }

    public function complete(): HabitCompletion
    {
        $completion = $this->completions()->create([
            'user_id' => $this->user_id,
            'completion_date' => now()->toDateString(),
            'xp_earned' => $this->xp_reward,
        ]);
        $this->increment('times_completed');
        $this->increment('current_streak');
        $this->user->addXP($this->xp_reward);
        $this->user->updateStreak();
        return $completion;
    }
}
```

