### 2.6 Badge Model
**File:** [app/Models/Badge.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/Badge.php)
Defines collectible rewards. The [checkAndAward()](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/Achievement.php#38-77) method automatically grants badges when requirements are met.
```php
class Badge extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = ['name', 'slug', 'description', 'icon', 'rarity', 'required_value', 'requirement_type'];

    public function users() { return $this->belongsToMany(User::class, 'user_badges')->withPivot('earned_at'); }

    public function checkAndAward(User $user): bool
    {
        if ($user->badges()->where('badge_id', $this->id)->exists()) return false;
        $meetsRequirement = match($this->requirement_type) {
            'streak' => $user->current_streak >= $this->required_value,
            'level' => $user->level >= $this->required_value,
            default => false,
        };
        if ($meetsRequirement) {
            $user->badges()->attach($this->id, ['earned_at' => now()]);
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

### 2.7 Achievement Model
**File:** [app/Models/Achievement.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Models/Achievement.php)
Defines milestones. Similar to Badges but tracks progress towards a goal.
```php
class Achievement extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = ['name', 'slug', 'description', 'icon', 'xp_reward', 'requirement_type', 'requirement_value'];

    public function users() { return $this->belongsToMany(User::class, 'user_achievements')->withPivot('progress', 'is_completed'); }

    public function checkAndAward(User $user): bool
    {
        // Logic to check requirements and award XP
        $meetsRequirement = match($this->requirement_type) {
            'first_habit' => $user->habits()->count() >= 1,
            'level' => $user->level >= $this->requirement_value,
            default => false,
        };
        if ($meetsRequirement) {
            $user->achievements()->syncWithoutDetaching([$this->id => ['is_completed' => true, 'completed_at' => now()]]);
            $user->addXP($this->xp_reward);
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

