## 3. Controllers

Controllers handle HTTP requests, validate input, call Model methods, and return responses. They act as the "Traffic Cops" between the User and the Database.

### 3.1 HabitController
**File:** [app/Http/Controllers/HabitController.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Http/Controllers/HabitController.php)
Manages the full lifecycle of user habits (CRUD + toggle completion).
```php
class HabitController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $habits = $request->user()->getTodayHabits();
        return view('habits.index', ['habits' => $habits]);
    }

    public function store(Request $request): RedirectResponse
    {
        $validated = $request->validate([
            'title' => 'required|string|max:255',
            'xp_reward' => 'required|integer|min:1|max:1000',
            'frequency' => 'nullable|in:daily,weekly',
        ]);
        Habit::create([
            'user_id' => $request->user()->id,
            'title' => $validated['title'],
            'xp_reward' => $validated['xp_reward'],
        ]);
        return redirect()->back()->with('success', 'Habit created!');
    }

    public function toggle(Request $request, Habit $habit): RedirectResponse
    {
        if ($habit->user_id !== $request->user()->id) abort(403);
        
        $existing = $habit->completions()->where('completion_date', today())->first();
        if ($existing) {
            $existing->delete();
            $habit->decrement('current_streak');
        } else {
            $habit->complete();
        }
        return redirect()->back();
    }

    public function destroy(Request $request, Habit $habit): RedirectResponse
    {
        if ($habit->user_id !== $request->user()->id) abort(403);
        $habit->delete();
        return redirect()->back()->with('success', 'Habit deleted!');
    }
}
```

### 3.2 QuestController
**File:** [app/Http/Controllers/QuestController.php](file:///Users/root1/Desktop/U/Github/Self_Dev/self-development/DevelopmentSeed/app/Http/Controllers/QuestController.php)
Manages quests with deadline tracking and difficulty-based XP multipliers.
```php
class QuestController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $userId = $request->user()->id;
        $dailyQuests = Quest::where('user_id', $userId)->where('type', 'daily')->get();
        $weeklyQuests = Quest::where('user_id', $userId)->where('type', 'weekly')->get();
        $bossQuests = Quest::where('user_id', $userId)->where('type', 'boss')->get();
        return view('quests.index', compact('dailyQuests', 'weeklyQuests', 'bossQuests'));
    }

    public function store(Request $request): RedirectResponse
    {
        $validated = $request->validate([
            'title' => 'required|string|max:255',
            'type' => 'required|in:daily,weekly,boss',
            'xp_reward' => 'required|integer|min:1|max:5000',
            'difficulty' => 'required|in:easy,medium,hard',
        ]);
        // Difficulty Multiplier
        $multiplier = match ($validated['difficulty']) {
            'easy' => 1, 'medium' => 1.5, 'hard' => 2, default => 1,
        };
        Quest::create([
            'user_id' => $request->user()->id,
            'xp_reward' => (int) ($validated['xp_reward'] * $multiplier),
            // ... other fields
        ]);
        return redirect()->back()->with('success', 'Quest created!');
    }

    public function complete(Request $request, Quest $quest): RedirectResponse
    {
        if ($quest->user_id !== $request->user()->id) abort(403);
        if ($quest->status !== 'completed') {
            $quest->complete();
            $request->user()->updateStreak();
        }
        return redirect()->back()->with('success', 'Quest completed! XP awarded!');
    }
}
```

